{"title":"Trek Adds All-New FX2 & FX3 To Hybrid Fitness Line of Bikes","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-new-fx2-fx3-hybrid-fitness-bikes/","date":1730297832000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-outta-the-saddle-jpeg.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" alt=\"(Photos / Trek Bikes)\" /></p>\n<p>To help their customers ride more, worry less, and live a “happier and healthier lifestyle”, <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/\" target=\"_blank\">Trek</a> has launched two new hybrid fitness bicycles. Introducing the new <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/hybrid-bikes/fitness-bikes/fx/fx-2-gen-4/p/40815/?colorCode=red\" target=\"_blank\">FX2</a> and <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/hybrid-bikes/fitness-bikes/fx/fx-3-gen-4/p/40819/?colorCode=blue\" target=\"_blank\">FX3</a>. trek says these two new models will bring more durability and capability to its fitness platform.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-beach-lean-jpeg-e1730224013599.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"955\" height=\"686\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-beach-lean-jpeg-e1730224013599.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes beach lean\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-beach-lean-jpeg-e1730224013599.webp 955w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-beach-lean-jpeg-e1730224013599-297x213.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-beach-lean-jpeg-e1730224013599-120x86.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-beach-lean-jpeg-e1730224013599-768x552.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>FX3 (Photos / Trek Bikes)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new FX models look to be versatile bikes that can handle some performance, as well as dish out some comfort and utility. They are feature-rich with lightweight aluminum frames, 1x Shimano CUES drivetrains, and a carbon fork on the FX3.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-Beach-lean-silver-jpeg-e1730224053151.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1036\" height=\"712\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-Beach-lean-silver-jpeg-e1730224053151.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes Beach lean silver\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-Beach-lean-silver-jpeg-e1730224053151.webp 1036w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-Beach-lean-silver-jpeg-e1730224053151-297x204.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-Beach-lean-silver-jpeg-e1730224053151-120x82.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-Beach-lean-silver-jpeg-e1730224053151-768x528.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>FX2</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Accessory Mounts</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes all the mounts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-all-the-mounts-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>New for the FX2 and FX3 are standard mounts for bags, racks, and fenders. Also, there are new additional mounts for a low-rider front rack and an Adventure Boss frame bag. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>More Durable Drivetrain</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes CUES drivetrain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-CUES-drivetrain-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Another new spec for the FX2 and FX3 is the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-cues-mid-tier-mtb-groups-intercompatible-9-10-11-speed-components-affordable-1x/\" target=\"_blank\">Shimano CUES</a> Drivetrain. The new CUES drivetrain is designed to be a rugged drivetrain that improves the riding experience with more riding and fewer shop visits.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Comfy and Active</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes streatch\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-streatch-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new FX2 and 3 utilize a less leisurely and more active riding position while maintaining riding comfort. It’s a riding position that lets the rider put more power to the pedals while staying safe, comfortable, and confident. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes cornering\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-cornering-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-chart-jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"482\" height=\"289\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-chart-jpg.webp\" alt=\"Trek Bikes FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes geo chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-chart-jpg.webp 482w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-chart-297x178.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-chart-120x72.webp 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-numbers-jpg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"547\" height=\"640\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-numbers-jpg.webp\" alt=\"Trek Bikes FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-numbers-jpg.webp 547w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-numbers-256x300.webp 256w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-Bikes-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-geo-numbers-103x120.webp 103w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>The Bikes</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-jpeg.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-jpeg.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes climbing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-jpeg.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-297x198.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-120x80.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-768x512.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-800x533.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-climbing-720x480.webp 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>The FX2 Gen 4</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $799</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sizes: XS, S, M, L, and XL</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX2-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224245957.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"742\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX2-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224245957.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes FX2 full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX2-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224245957.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX2-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224245957-297x172.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX2-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224245957-120x70.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX2-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224245957-768x445.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>The FX3 Gen 4</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $1,049</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sizes: XS, S, M, L, and XL</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX3-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224265513.webp\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1280\" height=\"746\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX3-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224265513.webp\" alt=\"Trek FX2 and FX3 Hybrid Bikes FX3 full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX3-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224265513.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX3-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224265513-297x173.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX3-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224265513-120x70.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Trek-FX2-and-FX3-Hybrid-Bikes-FX3-full-bike-jpeg-e1730224265513-768x448.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out all of the new 2025 bikes by hitting the link below.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/\" target=\"_blank\">TrekBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-new-fx2-fx3-hybrid-fitness-bikes/\">Trek Adds All-New FX2 &amp; FX3 To Hybrid Fitness Line of Bikes</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7ea2177d8477b19a3354f0282c5e5c2f1097663fed24a7c61d7afab382e588af","category":"Cycling"}